            <p>As Baki and Kakashi began planning, Temari pulled Naruto aside. "There's something you should know," she said quietly. "When Gaara was taken... he ordered the village not to pursue. He knew the risks, knew that sending shinobi after Akatsuki would mean more deaths. He made the choice to protect his people, even at the cost of his own life."</p>
            
